A 20-year-old man has died after being shot outside a Philadelphia concert being held to promote peace and stem violence in the city.

Police said the gunfire happened at about 8:30 p.m. Wednesday outside the Dell Music Center in the city's Fairmount Park area.

Officials said the man was arriving at the Philly Support Philly: Peace on the Streets concert when he got into an argument with someone in the parking lot.

